and finishing up with frisbee on the lawn.\nEvents in the Wednesday Evening Series are generally less challenging (both physically and navigationally) than many of our other events, and are therefore great for beginners and those less experienced with orienteering – while also offering a challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nCheck back later for special notes from the Course Designer(s). Lake Wilderness Park offers a interesting mix of open parkland and forested terrain crisscrossed with trails; there will be little to no off-trail travel necessary. The park is largely flat and sits on the northern shore of Lake Wilderness, with nice views of Mount Rainier when the weather allows."}
